<TITLE>Amarinder calls Kejriwal a sneaky little fellow, blames Akalis of corruption 5 hours ago</TITLE>
<TEXT>
Amritsar, Jan 29: With the Punjab Assembly Elections 2017 just round the corner, Congress chief ministerial candidate Captain Amarinder Singh on Sunday took a dig at Delhi Chief Minister Arvind Kejriwal and termed him as a sneaky little fellow. He further said that Kejriwal is very ambitious but thats not the ambition Punjab needs. Talking about Kejriwals win in 2014 polls, Amarinder said that is little wary of the Delhi Chief Minister as he cant take him for granted considering his victory in the 2014 polls. The state will go to vote on February 4 2017. 
 
Slamming the Akalis, Amarinder said they are total mismanagement, corruption, trade loss, farmers hanging themselves and the party it is a total collapse. Badal too old to understand & is busy doing his sangat darshan; giving step mother treatment to state, he added. 
  
