On being asked what if he loses, Congress CM candidate Captain Amarinder Singh was quoted by ANI saying he never fights an election that he doesnt win. He further added saying that he loves using social media as he love thinking and arguing if someone says something he dont think is correct. He said, 4 weeks I want to break drug nexus. We know who does it, it is question of govt being willing to do it. 
 
Recalling his decision of the 2004 Water Act, he was quoted by ANI saying that the reason for disagreeing to the construction of Satluj Yamuna Link Canal (SARYU) or SYL would have brought back terrorism in the state. Had I agreed to build the canal, I could guarantee that terrorism would have come back to Punjab. That is why I say that the Supreme Court does not understand what it is doing. You have to first decide what the quantum of water available to us is and whether Punjab has had done justice to it, Singh told ANI. 
 
The Congress Chief Ministerial candidate has also warned that Punjab will face a crisis similar to the 80s that saw the emergence of Khalistani movement. The movement being a Sikh nationalist movement demanded an independent state for Sikh people, if the Aam Aadmi Party (AAP) comes to power in the state. Singh expressed fear that if Arvind Kejriwal comes in to power, Punjab will again witness the unrest of the 80s crisis which killed around 35,000 Punjabis. In an interview to ANI, Singh alleged that the AAP cadre is accepting the extremist ideology and is accepting money from separatists.
